abwaanno.name: Qaamuuska Fiqi: Soomaali-Ingiriis - Cabdiraxmaan C. Xaashi, Cawil Cali Xaashi [1995]

a: a': (alif) the first letter of Somali al-phabet, according to the style adopted by this dictionary, it is a vowel letter ~ shaqal.
a': (suffix) [the] definite article of some masculine nouns. Ex. arag; aragga; the sight, in English, the indefinite articles are a and an and the definite article is the.

a': (suffix) —s; used to form the third person masculine plural present tense of verbs. Ex: friya; that looks..; maqla; that hears; hurda; that sleeps; Ex: xayawaanka cawska cuna...; animals that eats grass...
aa: aa': (n) long vowel of letter A. Ex: aabbe; father. Caano; milk.
aa?: (suffix); —ing; used to form the present continuous tense. Ex: ma socotaa; are you going; Wuu hurdaa; he is sleeping.
aabayeel: -ay / aabayeeshay: (v) respect (ris-pekt); consideration or courtesy. Ex: Waxba uma aabayeelin; he didn't respect anything ~ turid, —u aabayeel: (v) be considerate (bi kon-sidereyt); be thoughtful ~ tixgali —u aabayeelid -da: (n) consideration (kon-sidereyshin)
aabbanimo: -aabbanimada: (n) fatherhood (fader-huudh); the state of being a father.
aabbur: -ka: (n) lid (lid); cover (kaver); top ~ dabool, guf. Ex. aabburka ka qaad; take the lid off.
aabburan: -aabburnaa / aabburnayd: (adj) covered (koveridh); plugged (palaagid) ~ daboolan, gufeysan aabi -ga: (n) aggression (agreshen); the act of initiating a quarrel, a fight or an attack ~ gardarro, daandaasi aabuteey -ga: (n) kite (kayt) ~ warqadda cirka loo diro oo xariga leh
aabyood: ay /aabyootay: (v) provoke (pro-vowk). Ex: ku aabyood; incite to anger or resentment
aad: aad': (pronoun) you (vuu) ~ adi-ga. Ex: waraagdii aad keentay.... the letter you brought.
aad? -ay / day: (n) 1. go (goo). Ex: isbitaalka aad: go to the hospital. 2. aad: (adv) very (veeri); in a high degree; extremely, very much. Ex: aad u jarasan; very happy.
—aad': (suffix) -th; used to form ordinal numbers. Ex: afaraad; fourth (foorth); 4ih
aad iyo aad: (adv) extremely. (ikistrimli); very intense. Ex: aad iyo aad baan ugu baahnahay; I need it very much -isku aad -ka: (n) [sports] playoff also play-off. Ex: isku aadka kooxaha; the playoff of the teams —isku aaddi -yey / say: (V) align (alayn); to arrange in a line or line up. Ex: safka isku aaddi: line up
aadaab: aadaab-ta: (n) politeness (polaayt-nes); manners (man neris); etiquette (eti keeyt) ~ akhlaaq
aadaan: aadaan-ka: (n) the Muslim call to prayer, It is used to signify the time of prayer for the five obligatory prayers ~ addin.
aadan: (suffix): (v) if you not.... Ex. haddi aadan tagin...; if you don't
aaddan: -aa: (adj) [with preposition ku] 1. aligned (alaynidh); Ex: dheda ku aaddan; aligned in the middle. 2. due (duu); expected or scheduled ~ la filayo. Ex: bishee bay ku aaddan tahay; which month it's due (expected)
aaddi: -yey / say: (n) [with preposition kul align (a laayn); arrange in a line or line up. Ex: safka ku aaddi: keep in line -aad-daanaan -ta: (n) [ with preposition ku] 1. alignment also alignment (a-layn-ment); in parallel lines; opposite (op-pezit) ~ ka soo horjeed. 2. expected ~ la filayo.
aafee: -yey / aafeysay: (v) cause severe damage to something or someone
aafo: -da: (n) disaster (di-saas ter); catastrophe (ka taas taroofi); calamity (kalaamati); an event having fatal or ruinous results ~ masiibo, musiibo
aag: -ga: (n) 1. area (ee-riya); a region. Ex: aagga beeraha; the farming area. Aagga Xamar; the Xamar area. 2. nearby araes ~ u dhaw.
aaga: —aaga: (suffix) (possessive pronoun) with nouns having definite article —ga: ending. your (voor). Ex: buugaaga; your book. Caanahaaga; your milk. Qalinkaaga; your pen
aagaan: -ka: (n) 1. lid or cover used by the nomadic society ~ haruub. 2. small milk container
aakhir: -ka: (n) end (endi); conclusion (kon kuluu shin); completion (kom plit shin); Ex: aakhirka sheekada; the conclusion of the story
aakhirkii: (adv) ultimatly (ool-timeeytli); finally (faay-nali); eventually i•ven juwali) ~ aakhirutaankii.
aakhiro: -da: (n) hereafter (hiyer after); afterlife (after laay); judgement day (jajmant dheey); day of judgement ~ qiyaame
aakhirutaankii: (adv) ultimately (ool-timeeytli); finally (faaynali); eventually (i van juwali) ~ aakhirkii.
aalaa: (adv) often (often); usually (vush wali); regularly or customarily used ~ aalaaba, badanaaba
aalaaba: (adv) mostly (most li); generally (jena rali); usually vush wali) ~ aalaa
aalad: -da (n) instrument (inis tur mant); device (di vaays) ~ qalab
aaladee: -yey / aaladeysay: (v) equip (ikwip); supply with necessary tools aalkolo -aalkolada: (n) alcohol (alkahool) ~ aalkol
aammiin: -ta: (n) amen (ee man); used at the end of a prayer to beg for acceptance
aammin: 1. -ka: (n) trust (tarast); belief (bi-liif); confidence (kon-fi•dansi); faith (feeyth) ~ kalsooni, citiqaad.
2. aammin -ay / tay: (v) trust (tarast); Ex: haddaad aammintid wuu ku khayaamin; if you trust him, he will cheat you

aammin: -ka: (n) 1. trust (tarast); belief (bi-liif); confidence (kon fi dansi); faith (feeyth) kalsooni, citiqaad. 2. aammin -ay /tay: (v) trust (tarast); Ex: haddaad aammintid wuu ku khayaamin; if you trust him, he will cheat you
aammin-ka: (n) time (taaym) wakhti. Ex: waa ammin xun; it is a bad time
aamminaad: -da: (n) 1. trust (tarast); belief (bi-liif). 2. faith (feeyth) ~ citiqaad. 3. credibility (kere-dibiliti); confidence (kon fi dansi)~aamminid, kalsooni
aamminbax: -ay day: (v) [with preposition ka] mistrust (mis tarast); lack of trust or confidence aamminid la'aan, aammindarro. —la aamminikaro: (adj) trustworthy (tarast woor thi); reliable (ri laayabal) lagu kalsoonaan karo. Ex: Cali waa nin la aamminikaro; Ali is a trustworthy person
aammindarro: -da: (n) mistrust (mis tarast); lack of trust or confidence ~ aamminid la'aan, aamminbax. --Syn: uncertainty
aamminsan: -aa: (adj) believing (be lii ving); having a firm faith, confidence, or trust.
aammus: -ay / t ay: (v) shut up (shat ap); silence (saaylans); stop speaking ~ ha hadlin
aammusi: -yey / say: (v) silence (saay lansi); make silent or bring silence to someone or something
aan: aan: (pronoun) 1. me (mii); I (aay); us (aas); we (wii) used the speaking or writing person or persons ~ aannu. Ex: aan wax kuu sheego; let me tell something. 2. (clause pronoun) may I..., can I or let me ~ an. Ex: aan tago; let me go. Buuggaan aan qaato? can I take this book? Biyahaan aan cabbo? may I drink this water?
aan (suffix) I.. to the.. Ex: baankaan aadayaa; I am going to the bank

aan: (adverb) 1. used to express negation; not (nat); im-; in-; un-; il- Ex: aan faraxsanayn; unhappy. 2. suffix: (gadaalgale) -less: without; lacking. Ex: eedla'aan: blameless 3. -ness or -ment suffix: (gadaalgale) state; quality; condition; or degree of nouns derived from adjectives. Ex: aasnaan -ta; the state of being buried
aan daxalaysan: (adj) stainless (isteeyn les); without stain or blemish: Ex: bir aan daxalaysan; stainless steel
aan dhalan: (adj) unborn (an boon). Ex: ilma aan dhalan; an unborn child
aan dhammaanayn: (adj) infinite (infinit); not ending ~ aan xad lahayn
aan dhici karin: (adj) impossible (im poo-sibal) ~ aan suurtagal ahayn, Ex: waa wax aan dici karin in shaqadaan caawa la dhammeeyo; it is impossible to finish this job by tonight
aan islahayn: (adj) matchless (maajles); having no match or equal ~ aan isku habboonayan
aan kala jeclayn: (adj) indifferent (in dif rant)-, having or showing no preference ~ xumaan ama wanaag aan kala jeclayn
aan ku fillayn: (adj) insufficient (insafishanf) ~ naaqis ah. Ex: waxay siisay lacag aan ku fillayn; she gave him insufficient money
aan la dalban: (adj) unsolicited (ansolisitid) not requested ~ aan la wayddiisan
aan la hubin: (adj) uncertain (an ser tan)-, doubtful ~ aan sugnayn, shaki ku jiro
aan la ogolayn: (adj) unacceptable (an-aksep-tibal)-, unauthorized (an oo tha raaysid) ~ aan la fasaxin
aan la sheegin: (adj) 1. unannounced (an-anawn-sid) 2. unspecified (an ispe sifaayid) ~ aan la tilmaamin. Ex: wakhti aan la sheegin; unspecified time
aan la xallin: (adj) unresolved (an ri zoolvidy, unsolved (ansool-vidh) ~ aan weli xal loo helin
aan laga maarmikarin: (adj) indispensable (indispeensabal) ~ daruuri ah, lama huraan ah. Ex: qof aan laga maarmikarin ma jiro; nobody is indispensable. 2. essential (i-seen-shal)
aan lala socon: (adj) 1. unaccompanied (an akam panidh) ~ aan la wehelin. 2. unknown (an-nown)
aan macna lahayn: (adj) meaningless (miiningles); pointless (pooyntles) ~ aan wax ka soo qaad lahayn.
aan macquul ahayn: (adj) unreasonable {an rii sanabal)-, irrational (i raa shinaal) ~ aan caqli ahayn
aan milmayn: (adj) insoluble (in sol yabal), that which cannot be dissolved ~ aan qasmayn
aan muhiimad lahayn: (adj) insignificant (insignifikant)-, trivial (tirivaal); lacking in importance; unimportant ~ aan qiima lahayn
aan muran lahayn: (adj) indisputable (in dis biyuu tibal), ~ aan laysku khilaafi karin, xaqiiq ah
aan muuqan: (adj) hidden (hidhen)-, invisible (inviizibal); unseen (ansiin) ~ aan la arkayn
aan qaybsamin: (adj) indivisible (in di vi sabaV) ~ lakala qaybin karin
aan qiimo lahayn: (adj) 1. worthless (weerthlis)-, of no use or value ~ aan macna lahayn 2. cheap (jiip)
aan rasmi ahayn: (adj) informal (infoormal); unofficial (an o-fishaly, casual (kaashuwal) ~ aan caadi ahayn. Ex: shir aan rasmi ahayn; an informal meeting
aan sinnayn: (adj) uneven (an ii-van); rough (raf); unequal (an-ikwal) ~ aan isle'ekayn
aan waxbaran: (adj) uneducated (anejukeeytidh), ignorant (ig no rant) ~ see also [eeg] jaahil ah
aan xadaysnayn: (adj) unlimited (anlimitidh), indefinite (indhefanif) ~ aan caddayn, aan xadaysnayn. Ex: waxay maqnaan doontaa waqti aan xadaysnayn; she will be away for an indefinite period of time
aan xal lahayn: (adj) insoluble (insolyabal) impossible to solve; having no solution ~ aan la xallin karin. Ex: dhibaato aan xal lahayn; an insolvable problem. Ex: arrin aan xal lahayn; insoluble matter
aan xaq ahayn: (adj) 1. unjust (an-jast); not just; 2. unfair (anfeer) ~ aan caddaalad ahayn.
aanee: -yey / aaneysay: (v) [ with preposition u ] hold liable to; desire revenge; to spite; accuse (akiyuus)
aannan: (pronoun) not; we or I if ... not. Ex: haddii aannan imaan, iska tag; if I didn 't come, go. Ex: haddii annaan shaqaynin, lacag nala siin mayo; ifwe didn't work, we will not be paid.
aannu: (pronoun) let....us. Ex: Aannu u sheegno; let us tell him. Na keen aannu cashaynee; come on, let us have a dinner
aano: -aanada: (n) resentment (ri zent ment)-, anger (an ger)-, grievance aroused by something unjust, mean, or unworthy ~ godob, dakano
-aansho: (suffix)-. —ation: the result of an action or process. Ex: madoobaansho; the state of being black; dheeraansho; the state of being tall or long
aar: -ka: (n) 1. brave (bareeyv) ~ geesi. 2. (n) male lion (laayon) ~ libaax —u aar -ay / tay: (v) avenge (a-veenji); seek or take vengeance for another person
aaraa: -da: (n) 1. ideas (aay diyas) ~ fikrad. —Syn: thoughts, notions, concepts, conceptions. 2. opinions (opiin-yanis); a belief or conclusion ~ talo ama fikrad. —Syn: views, Ex: aaraa kala duwan baa la soo jeediyay; different ideas or opinions have been raised
aaran: aaran-ah: (adj) 1. prosperous (paros-peras); well-to-do; good time. Ex: sannad aaran ah; a prosperous year. 2. evergreen (evergriin). Ex: dhul aaran ah; an evergreen land
aardoon: -ka: (n) revenger (ri-veenjer); one who is seeking to take vengeance (ven-jansi)
aargalaan: -ka: (n) a large metal cup for drinking ~ kalax
aargudo: -aargutay / aargudatay: (v) seek or take vengeance for yourself; avenge (a-veeji); revenge (ri-veeji)
-u aargud: -ay / day: (v) seek or take vengeance for another person; avenge (aveenji) ~u aar
aariyee: -yey / say: (v) inflate (infaleeyt); fill something with air or gas
aarso: -aarsay I aarsatay: (v) revenge (ri veenji); avenge (aveenji); retaliate (ri-taali-yeeyt) seek or take vengeance for [oneself or another person]
aartilari: -ga: (n) artillery (aar tarleri); large-caliber weapons, such as cannon, howitzers, and missile launchers ~ sida madfac, kanooni ama hawser.
aaryo qaadasho: -qaadashada: (n) outing (aaw-ting); excursion (ikis-keer-shiri); a walk outdoors ~ aariyo qaadasho
aas: -ka: (n) 1. the act or process of burying; burial (beeriyal); funeral (fiyuunaral) ~ duug, xabaal
—aas -ay / tay: (v) 2. place in the ground; bury (beeri) ~ duug, xabaal
3. aas-ku: (n) sunset (san-set). Ex: aasku intuuna madoobaan; before the sunset [before it gets dark]
aasaas: -ka: (n) foundation (fawn-dheey-shin); base, basis, ground, groundwork ~ sal, bilow —aasaas -ay / tay: (v) establish (is taab-liish); set up; found
aasaasi: -ga: (n) 1. essential (i-sen-shel); fundamental (fan-dha-men-tai). 2. inherence or indispensable ~ lama huraan
aasan: -aa: (adj) buried (beeridh); placed in the ground ~ xabaalan ama duugan
aasbiriin: -ka: (n) aspirin (aas-periin). Ex: keniin aasbariin ah; an aspirin tablet
aashuun: -ka: (n) a large, often rounded, water vessel of earthenware ~ ashuun, jalxad
aasnaan: -ta: (n) a condition or state of being buried
-aato: (suffix)-, if she... Ex: hadday jeclaato; if she likes; hadday fiicnaato; ifshe gets better
aawaday: (preposition) for my sake ~ dartay. Ex: waxay u joogeen aawaday; they stayed for my sake
aawadeed: (preposition) for it's or her sake ~ darteed, awgeed
aawadiis: (preposition) 1. for his sake - dartiis, awgiis 2. because of
aaway?: [aawey] (adv) where? (weer); at or in what place?. Ex: Aaway taleefoonkii? where is the telephone?
aawaye?: (adv) [aaweye] where are they? - meeye. Ex: Carruurtii aawaye? where are the children?
aay: -ey / day: (v) [with preposition u] benefit (bene fit)-, derive advantage from something at later time
aayad: -da: (n) koranic verse; an individual verse in the Quran
aayar: (adv) slowly (islowli); taking more time than is usual or necessary — tartiib, qunyar. Ex: Aayar u soco; walk slowly. —Syn: dilatory, leisurely, laggard, deliberate
aayatiin: -ka: (n) 1. fate (feyt); destiny (destani); predetermined events - calaf, aaye, aayo. -Syn:, kismet, lot, portion. 2. future (fiyuujar) - mustaqbal ama mustaqbil
aaye: -aayaha: (n) fate (feyt); predetermined events - see also [eeg] aayatiin
aayo: -aayaha: (n) fate (feyt); predetermined events - see also [eeg] aayatiin
aayo: aayada: (n) 1. stepmother (isteep maadar); the wife of one's father or uncle. 2. aunt (aanti); the sister of one's father - eeddo. 3. u aayo: benefit (bene fit) - see also [eeg] u aay
ab: -ka: (n) forefather (foorfaathar); ancestor (aan ses ter) ~ isir, walcan, sullan
abaabul: -ka: (n) 1. organization (oorgenizeeyshin). 2 -abaabulka: (adj) organizational. Ex: guddiga abaabulka; organizational committee. 3. —abaabul -ay /
abaad: -ay I day: (v) lost (loosti); no longer in the possession for a long time - abaaji. Ex: xoolihii abaaday; the lost livestock
abaahi: -yey: (v) mate (meeyt); pair animals [especially camels] for breeding - u hay, kud
abaaji: -yey / say: (v) lost (loosti); no longer in the possession for a long time - abaad

aynan: (v) [; 'gative with ma] we ... not. Ex ma aynan arag; we didn't see. 1a aynan maqal; we didn't hear

ayno: (suffix): [with negative ma plus ayno = mayno or maynu] we ... not ... with past continuous tense Ex: shaqayn mayno ; we are not working, seexan mayno; we are not sleeping

ays: (suffix): -ation; or ing; action or process. Ex: ilays; lightening
aysaa: (suffix) [negative with ma, miyaad or miyay] used to form negative present continuous tense of some verbs with pronoun you or she. Ex: miyaad tagaysaa? are you leaving? Ma shaqaynaysaa? are you working?

dawakhsan: -aa / nayd: (adj) dizzy (disi); disoriented (dis-oori-yentidh)-, giddy (gidhi) ~ dammaadsan, dawaqsan Ex: waan dawakhsan nahay; 1 am feeling dizzy
dawarsi: -ga: (n) street-begging; panhandling (paan-han-dhel-ingl); begging (beeg-ing) ~ dewarsi, tuugsi, baryid, Ex: dawasigu halkaan waa ka mamnuuc; begging is not allowed here
dawdawle: -dawdawlaha: (n) talker (tooker) ~ warbadne Ex: Ismaaciil waa dawdawle; Ismail is a talker
dawee: -yey / daweysay: (v) cure (kiyuur); remedy (ramedi); heal (hiil); treat medically. Ex: dawee bukaanka; cure the patient
da'weyn: -aa / nay: (adj) old (oldh) ~ duq. Ex: nin da 'wayn; an old man
dawli: -ah: (adj) 1. governmental (gavar-mental) Ex: xukun dawli ah; governmental law ~ dowli. 2. dawli -ga: (n) rope (roop), especially one used to bring water out of wells ~ xarig
dawo: -dawada: (n) medicine (meda-sin); medication (medi-keey-shiri); drug (daraag); remedy (ramedi) ~ daawo. Ex: wax dawo ah ma qaadataa? do you take any medication?
daxal: daxal -daxalaystay / daxalaysatay: (v) become corroded; corrode (korowdh); rust (raast)~ mirir, Ex: bir daxalaysatay; a rusted iron
day: (v) look (luuk), see (sii); glance (galaansi) ~ dey, eeg, fiiri. Ex: day wiilkaas; look at that boy —isku day -ey / day: (v) try on (taraay on); try out; test experimentally ~ isku jimee
dayaafad: -da: (n) hospitality (hos-pitaaliti); feast (fiist); banquet (bankuwit); entertainment (inter-teey-menf) ~ diyaafad, marti-gelis, soo-dhawayn-ta
dayaan: -ka: (n) 1. echo (eekow) ~ jabaq-celis. 2. —dayaan dayaamay/ dayaantay: (v) disoriented (dis-oori-yentidh); dizzy (diisi); feel dizzy ~ dayoob. Ex: waan dayaamay; I become dizzy
dayaarad: -da: (n) airplane (eer-paleeynn); aeroplane (eero-paleeyn); aircraft (eer-karaaft); airliner (eer-laayner) ~ dayuurad, diyaarad
dayac: -ay / day: (v) neglect (nig-lekt); fail to care; neglect one's duty; ignore one's obligations ~ layac, isku lad
dayacid: —dayacan -dayacnaa / dayacnayd: (adj) neglected (nig-lektidh); uncared for; unprotected (an-paro-tektidh); left alone
dayactir: -ka: (n) 1. maintenance (meeyn-tanansi); upkeep (ap-kiip); repair (ri-peer). 2. spare parts (paartis); components for maintenance ~ dayactirid
dayactir -ay / tay: (v) maintain (meeyn-teeyn); keep in good repair (ri-peer); service (ser-vis); keep up
da'yar: -ta: (n) young (yaang); youth (yuuth) ~ dhallinyaro —da'yar -ah: (adj) young (yaang). Ex: gabadh da 'yar; a young girl
dayasho: -dayashada: (n) [with preposition ku] imitation (imi-teey-shin); copying (kaap-ing) ~ ku dayasho
dayicid: -da: (n) negligence (nig-le-jansi); carelessness (keer-les-nes); undutifulness (an-dhuuti-fuul-nes); neglect (nig-lekt) ~ dayacaad, isku-ladid
daymasho: -daymashada: (n) the act of borrowing or getting a loan ~ amaahasho
dayoow: -dayoobay / dayowday: (v) 1. be bewildered (bi-wil-dheridh); experience disorientation; feel disoriented (dis-oori-yentidh); 2. be dizzy (diisi); feel dizzy ~ dayaan
dayr: -ta: (n) autumn (oo-tem); fall (fool) ~ xilliga ama fasalka dayrta. Ex: dayrtaan baan rabaa inaan Xamar tago; I will be going to Mogadishu this autumn
dayri: -yey / say: (v) disown (dis-own); repudiate (ri-puu-diyeeyt); especially a child
dayro: -dayrada: (n) 1. repudiation (ri-puu-diyey-shin) the act of disowning [a child, for example], 2. lying about one's own assets, to avoid giving some away
dayuus: -ka: (n) ; immoralist (i-moora-liist); bad person; bad guy; unprincipled male; one without morals; rascal (raas-kal); villain (vi-lan)
dayuusad: -da: (n) bad woman or girl - see also [eeg] dayuus
debci: -yey/say: (v) relax(ri-laaksi);: loosen up (luu-sen ap); ease up (iizap) ~ jilci
debecsan: -aa / nayd: (adj) loose (luus); relaxed (ri-laaksidh); soft (sooft); unfixed (an-fiksidh) ~ jilicsanaan. Ex: bool debacsan; a loose bolt
ded: ded -ay / day: (v) roof (ruuf); cover (kofer) ~ dabool —deddan: (adj) covered (ka-veridh) ~ daddan. Ex: walax deddan; something covered
deddeji: -yey / say: (v) rush (rash); hasten (heey-sen); speed up; accelerate (ak-sala-reeyt); expedite (ekis-pi-dhaayt) ~ dedeji
deegaan: -ka: (n) 1. settlement (setalment); environment (envaayroment); residence (rezi-densi); domicile (dhomo-saayl) ~ dagaan, degaan, bey'ad, hooy. 2. regional state
deeq: -da: (n) grant (garaant); donation (doo-neey-shin); contribution (kon-tiri-biyuu-shin); charity (jaa-rati); gift (gift) ~ sadaqo
deeqa: -y / deeqday: (adj) adequate (a-dik-wit); sufficient (sa-fi-shant) ~ ku filan. Ex: sahaydu way deeqdaa; the supplies are adequate
deeqdaran: -aa: (adj) giving or spending reluctantly; stingy (stin-ji); close-fisted (kalows-fistidh); ungenerous (an-jena-res) -bakhayl
deeqsi: -ga: (n) generous giver (jene-ras gi-ver); benefactor (bene-fak-ter); unselfish donor; liberal giver ~ sikhi,
deeqsii: -yey / say: (v) make sufficient or adequate; suffice (sa-faays); satisfy (satis-faay)
deeqsinimo: -deeqsinimada: (n) generosity (jeno-roosati); generous act; generous giving; bounty (bawntii); benevolence (bene-va-lensi)
deg: -ay / tay: (v) 1. get down, descend. Ex: Cali, soo deg!; Ali, come down!

ku deg: (v) land on 2. move in; settle (satai); reside (ri-zeeydh). Ex: waxaan degnay guri cusub; we moved in to a new house. 3. sink (sink); run aground (a-garaawndh); go under; submerge (sab-meerji). Ex: markabkii waa degay; the ship went under
degaan: -ka: (n) settlement (setalment); residence (rezi-densi); accommodation (a-koma-deey-shin); environment (envaayroment); domicile (dhomo-saayl); habitation ~ deegaan, bey'ad, hooy, degmo. Ex: Gurigaan degaan kuma fiicna; this building is not fit for habitation
degaandag: -ga: (n) inclined surface; slope (islowp); ramp (raamp); downhill (dhaawn-hiil) ~ hoos u-janjeera
degasho: -degashada: (n) the act of climbing down or getting down
degdeg: -ta: (n) urgency (er-jensi); haste (heeyst); hurry (he-ri); rush (rash)', immediacy (i-midi-yasi); emergency (imeer-jensi)

degdeg -ah: (adj) urgent (eer-jent); immediate (imi-di-yeeyt); quick (kuwik); instant (in-istent); hasty (heeysti); in a hurry; express (ikis-parees)-dhakhso. Ex: xaalad degdeg ah; an urgent situation
degdeg siinyo: -siinyaha: (n) haste (heeyst); rush (rash) ~ degdeg. Ex: haddii aad degdegsiinyo ku guursatid, waxaa laga yaabaa inaad ka shallaydid; Ifyou marry in haste, you may regret it later
degdegsan: -aa / ayd: (adj) in a hurry; unable to wait; urgent (eer-jent) ~ dagdagsan. Ex: wuu degdegsan yahay; he is in a hurry
deggan: -aa / ayd: (adj) 1. calm (kaalm); peaceful (piis-ful); tranquil (taraang-kuwil); undisturbed (an-dis-teer-bidh); quiet (ku-waayt); easy-going place. Ex: baddu way deggan tahay; the sea is calm; meel deggan; quiet place. 2. dwell in (du-weel in); reside at (ri-2aaydh at); be occupied (bii oki-paayidh); inhabit (in-habit); live at- daggan, ku nool. Ex: Ali waxuu deggan yahay magaalada; Ali lives in the city
degid: -da: (v) 1. the act of sinking down or going under ~ quusid, degitaan, degis. 2. the act of settling 3. the act of landing (laanding); descending. Ex: degida dayuuradaa; the landing of airplanes
degitaan: -ta: (n) habitation (haabateyshin) ~ degis, Ex: waxaa doonayaa inaan soo eego inuu gurigu degitaan ku haboon yahay; I would like to see whether the house is fit for habitation. ~ see also [eeg] degid
dego: -degtay / degatay: (v) go down (dhaawn); go or come down; descend (di-sendi); get out. Ex: hoos bay u degatay; she went down
degsan: -aan / ayd: (adj) established (istaabi-liishidh). Ex: sharci degsan; an established law
deji: -yey / say: (v) 1. comfort (kam-fort) a person ~ sasabid. 2. unload (anlowdh); bring down Ex: baabuurka alaabta ka soo daji; unload the stuff from the car. 3. accommodate (akamu-dheeyt); Ex: reerka meel deji; accommodate the family —soo deji -yey / saay: (v) import (impoort)
deked: -da: (n) harbor (haar-bar); also harbour; port (poort); seaport (siipoort), dock (dhaak); wharf (woorf) ~ furdo, dakad
dekreeto: -dekreetada: (n) decree (dik-rii); order (oor-dher); command (komaandh) ~ amar. Ex: dekreeto madaxweyne... presidential decree...
deldel: -ay / deldeshay: (v) hang (haang); put a person to death by hanging; crucify (kuruu-sifaay); lynch (linji)
dembi: -ga: (n) crime (karaaym); offense also offence (o-feensi); sin (sin); misdeed (mis-dhiidh); wrongdoing (roong-dhu-wing) ~ dambi, danbi, falxun
dembi dhaaf: -ka: (n) the act of forgiving or excusing; pardon (paar-dhen); forgiveness (fer-giv-nes); amnesty (aam-nest); absolution (ab-suuli-shin) ~ cafis Ex: dambi dhaafku waa fiican yahay; the forgiveness is good
u dambi dhaaf -ay / tay: (v) forgive (feer-giv) someone; excuse (ekis-kiyuuz); condone (kon-doori) ~ cafi, saamax, masaamax
dembiile: -dembiilaha: (n) criminal (kirmi-nal); offender (o-feen-dher); perpetrator (per-patreeytar) of a crime; felon (fe-lari); law-breaker; delinquent (di-lin-kuwent); sinner (si-ner) ~ dambiile, danbiile. Ex: waa dembiile; he is a criminal
demi: -yey / say: (v) 1. switch off (iswiij of); turn off (teen of). 2. extinguish (ekistinguwiish); put out a fire ~ bakhtii
denbi: -ga: (n) crime (karaaym); offense also offence (o-feensi); sin (sin); misdeed (mis-dhiidh); wrongdoing (roong-dhu-wing) ~ dambi, danbi, falxun
densan: -aa: (adj) switched off (iswiijidh of); turned off (teenidh of)
derejo: -derejada: (n) 1. grade (gareeydh); rank (raangk); position (posi-shin) ~ garaado. Ex: waa maxay derejadiisu? What is his rank? 2. respect (rispakt) - xurmo. 3. degree (digrii) ~ heer kul
deris: -dersay / deristay: (v) study (stadhi); examine (igzaamin); investigate (in-vesti-geeyt). Ex: deris sababta ay ku dhacday! Investigate to find out the reason why it happened!
deris -ka: (n) neighbor (neey-bor); neighborhood (neey-bor-huudh) ~ daris, jaar, jiiraan
dewersi: -ga: (n) street-begging; panhandling (paan-han-dhel-ing); begging (beeg-ing) ~ dawarsi, tuugsi, baryid. Ex: dewarsigu halkaan waa ka mamnuuc; begging is not allowed here
deyd: -ka: (n) 1. courtyard (koort-yaadh); yard (yaadh). 2. enclosure (en-kalaaw-sher); fence (feens) ~ xero, deyr
deymo: -deyntay / deymatay: (v) borrow (baaroow); take on loan (loown); take on credit; get credit ~ deynso
deymi: -yey / say: (v) lend (lendh); loan (loown); give or grant one a loan; give credit ~ amaahin. Ex: Fadlan ma i daymin kartaa $50? Could you lend me $50, please?
deyn: -ta/ka: (n) loan (loown); credit (kare-dit); debt (dheet), liability (laaya-biliti); something owing; mortgage (moor-geeyj) ~ amaah
deynso: -densaday / deynsatay: (v) borrow (baaroow); take on loan (loown); take on credit; get credit
deyr: -ka: (n) 1. courtyard (koort- yaadh); yard (yaadh) ~ daarad. 2. enclosure (en-kalaaw-sher) fence (feens) ~ deyd, xero
deyso: -deystay / deysatay: (v) keep it for your self ~ iska deyso
dh: -da: (n) the fouth (4th) letter of the Somali alphabet, according to the style adopted by this dictionary, it is a consonant letter ~ shibbane
dhaadhac: -a: (n) 1. slope (isloop) dagaandeg. 2. income (inkam); extra income. Ex: shaqada dhaadhac makaa soo galaa? do you get extra income from the job? 3. soo dhaadhac (v) come down. Ex: magaalada u soo dhaadhac; come down into the city.
dhaadheer: -aa: (adj) tall (tool); high (haay). Ex: sarihii dhaadheeraa; the tall buildings
dhaadhici: -ay say: (v) 1. lower / (loower); to cause to come down gradually. Ex: hoos u dhaadhici; lower it down. 2. ka dhaadhici - yey/sey: (v) convince (kon-viinsi); persuade (peer-suweeydh); make believe
dhaaf: -ay / tay: (v) 1. leave alone (liiv aloon); Ex: iska dhaaf, hataaban; leave it alone, don't touch. 2. pass (paas); move by. Ex: baabuurkaas dhaaf; pass that car. 3. is dhaafi yey/ say: (v) pass it to someone else; get rid of. 4. make the sign of a cross. 5. is dhaafsi ga: (n) exchange (ikis-janji); trade (tareeydh). Ex: is dhaafsiga lacagta qalaad; the foreign currency exchange
dhaafid: -da: (v) overtake (oowvar- teyk); the act of passing ka hor marid. Ex: baabuur dhaafid badnidaa; You are overtaking too many cars
dhaadhaaf: -ay/tay: (v) 1. cross from one side to the other, again and again; zig zag. 2. is dhaadhaafi - ay/ say: (v) ignore (ignoor); pay no attention to; disregard (dis-ri- gaardh) iska dhegatir
dhaafsii: -yey: (v) make someone cross; Ex: carruurta jidka dhaafsii; cross the children to the street
dhaafsiisan: -aa: (adj) 1. beyond (biyaand); on the far side of; past, Ex: meel guriga dhaafsiisan; a place beyond the house. 2. in addition to: Ex: wax intaa dhaafsiisan miyaad rabtaa? do you need something in addition to that?
dhaafso: -dhaafsaday/dhaafsatay: (v) trade (tareeydh); swap (iswaap); make an exchange of one thing for another
dhaaji: -yey / say: (v) mimic (mimik); ape (eeyp); ridicule (ridi-kiyuul); mock (maak), taunt (toont) ~ canjil
dhaan: -ka: (n) 1. water fetching; especially using a camel loaded with water vessels. 2. dhaan -dhaamay / dhaantay: (v) become better; feel better; improve (impuruuv). Ex: sidii hore waan dhaamaa; 1 feel better now
dhaandhaan: -ka: (n) idiot (idh-yat); foolish or stupid person ~ nacas, sawir
dhaar: dhaar -tay / atay: (v) swear an oath; take one's oath
dhaari: -yey / say: (v) take one's oath; cause someone to speak on oath. Ex: markhaatiyaashii oo dhan waa la dhaariyey; All the witnesses have been sworn
dhaaro: -dhaartay / dhaaratay: (v) swear an oath; take one's oath
dhaarsan: -aa / ayd: (adj) sworn in (swoorn in); under oath
dhaasho: -dhaashaday / dhaashatay: (v) put cream on one's face
dhaawac: dhaawac -ay / day: (v) injure (in-jar); hurt (heert); harm (haarm); wound (wuundh); inflict wound ~ wax-yeellayn
dhaawicid: -da: (n) the act of injuring or inflicting a wound
dhaawacmid: -da: (n) the act of being wounded or injured
dhaaxaan: (adv) often (ofan); many times; frequently. Ex: dhaaxaan ku iri ha samayn! I told you often not to do that!
dhab: dhab -ah: (adj) 1. real (ri-yal); true (turuu); genuine (jeniwin); authentic (o-then-tik) ~ rasmi. Ex: waa harag dhab ah; this is genuine leather. 2. serious (siiriyas). Ex: -waa iga dhab, ciyaari mayo; I am serious, I am not joking
dhab -ta: (n) lap (laap); laps ~ Ex: dhabtayda ku soo fariiso; sit on my lap
dhaban: dhaban -ka: (n) even number (iivan nam-ber). Ex: sida 2,4,6; such as 2, 4, 6
dhabannaano: -dhabannaanada: (n) slap (islaap); a sharp blow made with the open hand to the face
dhabar: -ka:: (n) back (baak); dorsum (door-sem). Ex: dhabar kuu u yiilay ama jiifay; He was lying on his back
dhabarjabi: -yey I say. (v) 1. break one's back. 2. exhaust (ig-zoost); wear out completely ~ daali
dhabarjabin: -ta: (v) forces for outflanking or maneuvering around and behind the back of an opposing force [enemy]
dhabbacan: -dhabbacnaa / dhabbacnayd: (adj) lying with the front or with the belly [abdomen]; prone (parown)
dhabbaggal: -ay/dhabbaggashay: (v) [with preposition u] (v) find the facts; observe carefully ~ u dhabbaggal
dhabbe: -dhabbaha: (n) footpath (fuut-paath); path (paath); road, street, way ~ dhabo, wadiiqo, jid, marin
dhabbo: -dhabbada: (n) footpath (fuut-paath)-, oath (paath)-, road, street, way, ~ dhabbe, wadiiqo, jid, marin
dhabcaal: -ah: (adj) 1. miserly (maysarli); stingy (istinji) ~ bakhayl, gacan adag, bakhiil, qudur. -Syn: close-fisted, niggardly, penny-pinching, miserly, parsimonious, penurious, tight, tightfisted. Ex: ninka dhabcaal ah; the stingy man. 2. dhabcaal -ka: (n) miser (maysar).
dhabee: -yey / dhabeysay: (v) [with preposition ka] prove (puruuv); make it happen; put to the proof; substantiate ~ ka dhabee. Ex: hadal lama rabee ka dhabee; don't talk about it, just prove it
dhabiil: -ay / dhabiishay: (v) not help; refuse to help, especially a shared work
dhabiiltan: -ka: (n) the act of refusing to help, especially a shared work
dhaboob: -ay / dhabowday: (v) became true; has became true ~ rumow. Ex: sheekadii way dhabowday; the story has became true
dhabqi: -yey/say: (v) 1. disturb (dis-teerb); put out of tempo or rhythm; especially while dancing or playing music ~ foorteembo samee. 2. heckle (he-kal); badger (baa-jer) ~ qas
dhabxanag: -ga: (n) palate (paalet)-, hard palate; soft palate ~ dhanxarag
dhac: dhac: -dhacay I dhacday: (v) 1. fall (fool), drop or come down freely to the ground. Ex: dhulkuu ku dhacay; he fell to the ground. 2. expire (ekis-paayar) ~ waqtigiisii dhammaaday. Ex: Baasaboor dhacay; expired passport. 3. fail (feel)-, Ex: Imtixaankii way ku dhacday; she failed the examintion. 4. happen (ha-pin); take place or occur by chance. Ex: maxaa dhacay? what happened? 5. rob (rob); engage in or commit robbery. Ex: tuug baa dhacay; the thief robbed her. 6. decline (dikalaayn); in financial value. Ex: Sanadkii dhawaa, qiimaha doolarku aad buu u dhacay; last year, dollar prices fell sharply. 7. ku dhac -ay / day: (v) collide (kolaaydh); come into collision or direct impact with; bump against; smash into. Ex: laba baabuur baa isku dhacday; two cars had collided
dhacaan: dhacaan:- dhacaamay / dhacaantay: (v) secrete (se-kiriit); sap (saap); exude (eg-zuudh)
dhacadiid: -ay / day: (v) lie (laay); be or place oneself at rest in a flat, horizontal, or back position ~ dhacdiid
dhacdiidan: -dhacdiinaa / dhaciidnayd: (adj) supine (su-paayn); lying on the back ~ jeego-jeego u jiifa
dhacdhac: -a: (n) Income (inkam); extra income ~ Ex: shaqada dhadhac makaa soo galaa? do you get extra income on the job?
dhacdhac: -ay / day: (v) sway (isweey); move or walk from side to side with a swinging motion
dhacdo: -dhacdada: (n) event (i-vent); incident (insidhent); happening (hapa-ning); occurrence (okarensi); a scene (sim)
dhacsii: -yey / say: (v) make someone understand; explain (ikis-paleeyn); elucidate (i-uu-sidheeyt); clarify (ka-laara-faay) ~ ka dhaadhacsii, u bayaani
dhacso: -dhacsaday / dhacsatay: (v) retake (ri-teeyk); recapture (ri-kap-jar); regain stolen properties ~ soo dhacso
dhad: -ay / day: (v) fade (feeydh); lose freshness; wither (wi-ther); droop (dhuruup) ~ Ex: ubaxii xagaaga ee dhaday; summer flowers that had faded
dhadhaab: -ka:: (n) large rock (laarj rook), boulder (bool-dhar) ~ dandaan, dhagax weyn
dhadhami: -yey / say: (v) taste (teeyst); have a taste; savor (seey-ver); find palatable (aali-tibol) ~ dhandhami, dhedhami. Ex: sidee u dhadhamaysaa? how does it taste?
dhadhamo: -dhadhamada: (n) tasting at once, usually small quantity of milk; taste (teeyst); flavor (faleey-ver); aftertaste (after-teeysf) ~ dhadhan
dhado: -dhadada: (n) mist (mist); dew (dhuu); hoarfrost (hoor-foosf); white frost ~ dhedo, dharab
dhaf: -ay / tay: (v) [with preposition isku] mix (miksi); blend (baleendh) ~ isku qas, isku dhaf Ex: ha isku dhafin ciida iyo shamiitada; don't mix the sand and the cement
dhafaag: -ga: (n) mush (maash); something thick, soft, and pulpy ~ qoosh
dhafandhaaf: -ka: (n) reciprocation (ri-sip-ri-keey-shin); alternation (ol-ter-neey-shin); to and fro movement ~ talantaali
dhafar: - dhafray / dhaftay: (v) stay awake late at night Ex: xalay shaqaan ku dhafray; I was awake last night working
dhafoor: -ka: (n) temple (tem-pal); the flat region on either side of the forehead
dhaga adag: -dhaga adkaa / dhaga adkayd: (adj) disobedient (dis-o-biidi-yant); rebellious (ri-beel-yes); disobeying (dis-o-beeying); naughty (nooti); obstinate (o-bis-tineeyt) ~ dhega adag, canaadi
dhaga culus: (adj) hard of hearing; having hearing problem
dhagaati: -ga: (n) string (istring); a cord used for fastening, tying, or lacing
dhagar: dhagar -dhagray/dhagartay: (v) cheat (jiit); deceive (disiiv); mislead, betray, khayaan, khiyaan
dhagar qabe: dhagar qabaha: (n) dishonest or crooked man; deceiver (diziiver); swindler (swindhalar); rascal (raaskal); cheater (jiiter) ~ khayaanoole, khaayin; khayaanalow, khaa'in,
dhagarre: -dhagarraha: (n) dishonest or crooked man; .deceiver (zfenver); swindler (swindhalar) ~ dhagar qabe, dhagarlow
dhagax: -a: (n) stone (istoori); rock (raak) —dhagax leh: (adj) stony (istooni). Ex: meel dhagax leh baan tegnay; we went into stony place
dhagaxyee: -yey I dhagxyeysay: (v) stone (istoon); hurl or throw stones at

oo: long vowel of the letter o of the Somali alphabet

urursan: -aa / ayd: (adj) collective (ko-lek-tiv); united (yu-naaytid), organized (or-ga-naay-zid); arranged (a-reeynjid) ~ wadajira, nidaamsan
us: (interjection)', stop speaking; shut up! ~ shib dheh
usbuuc: -a: (n) week (wiik) ~ asbuuc, toddobaad. Ex: laba usbuuc; two weeks
usbuucle: -ha; (n) weekly (wiikli). Ex: wargeys usbuucle ah; a weekly newspaper
Ustareeliya: (n) Australia (oos-taree-liya)-, Canberra is the capital and Sydney is the largest city ~ Awstaraaliya
uu: (n) long vowel of u letter of Somali alphabet. Ex: uurka; the pregnancy (pareg-nan-si)

uun -ka; (n) the creations of God [Allah] ~ khalqi

uurkuhar: -ka (n) a baby bom after the death of his father
uurkutaallo: -uurkutaallada: (n) resentment (ri-zant-ment); rage (reeyj); anger (aang-ger); exasperation (ig-zaas-pa-reey-shin) ~ urug, urugo, caro, umal, xanaaq

waa: -ga: (n) time (taaym); epoch (epek); era (eera); particular period of time or a season ~ xilli, ayaan seben, wakhti, samaan, seman. Ex: waa wakhtiyada kamid ah; once upon a time

waa -yey / wayday / waayeen / waynay: (v) cannot find; unable to find ~ waay, wey. Ex: furihii waan waayey; I could not find the key
waa: (pronoun) this (this); used to refer, what is about. Ex: kani waa maxay? waa guri; what is this? this is a house
waa hagaag: (adj) okay (oo-tey); OK; alright (ool-raayt); all right ~ waayahay
waa inaan: (expression) I have to. Ex: waa inaan u yeeraa; I have to call him —waa inuu: he has to —waa inaad: you have to —waa inay: they have to / she has to
waab: -ka: (n) hut (hat), shack (shaak); shelter made of tree branches; makeshift dwelling ~ buul
waabaayo: -waabaayada: (n) poison (pooy-san); toxicity (tok-siisiti); toxic agent; poisonousness; venom (veenom); toxicant; toxin ~ sun
waabari: -ga: (n) daybreak (deey-bareeyk); dawn (doon); morning (moon-ing); crack of dawn ~ waabberi
waabasho: -waabashada: (n) the act of dodging or ducking; dodge (dhaaj); duck (dhak) ~ gabbasho

waabso: -waabsaday I waabsatay (v) try to decieve some one by pretending to be stronger, bluff (balaaf)
waad: waad: (pronoun you plus action verb) you... Ex: waad tiri; you said that, waad maqashay; you heard that
waadax ah: (adj) clear (kili-yar); explicit (ikis-pili-sit); obvious (oob-vi-yas); crystal-clear; manifest (maane-fest) ~ si cad
waadi: -ga: (n) stream bed (istiriim beedh); gorge (goorj); canyon (kaanyari); river valley; wadi also wady ~ tog, doox
waafaji: -yey I say: (v) bring into agreement; harmonize (haar-ma-naayz); reconcile (re-kon-saayl); make conform.
is waafajin -ta: (n) reconciliation (rekansiliyey-shin); conformity (kon-foor-mati); matching; fitting ~ iswaafajin
waafaq: -ay / day: (v) accept (aksept); admit (adhmit); consent (kon-sent); agree (agrn) ~ oggolow, aqbal
waafaqsan: -aa / ayd: (adj) agreeing (agrii-ing); consistent with; in conformity; concurrent (kon-ka-ranf)
waafi: -ah: (adj) good quality. Ex: harag waafi ah; a good quality leather

waalo: -waashay I waalatay: (v) become mad, crazy, insane or mentally disturbed ~ see also [eeg] waalan
waan: (pronoun I plus action verb) I ... to. Ex: waan ku jeclahay; I love you. waan ka xumahay: (expression) I am sorry (soori).
waani: -yey / say: (v) give or offer advice to; advise (adh-veeyz); counsel (kaawn-sal); make a suggestion - la tali, u naseexee
waano: -waanada: (n) advice (adh-veeyz)-, counsel (kaawn-sal), guidance (gaay-densi); piece of advice; suggestion (saj-jesh-shari), opinion (o-piin-yan) ~ talo, nasteexo

waasac: -ah: (adj) spacious (ispeeysshes); roomy (ruumi) ~ fitaax, fataaxsan, fataax — Syn: ample, capacious, commodious
Waashinton: (n) Washington (waashin-tan); the capital city of the United States
waasici: -yey / say: (v) make larger; expand (ikispaandi) ~ fitaaxi, ballaari, fataaxi
waax: -da: (n) part (paart), share (sheer), division (di-vishin), section (sek-shin); sector (sek-tar); department (di-paart '-ment) ~ qeyb, wakaalad. Ex: waaxda caafimaadka; the health department
waay: -yey / wayday / waayeen / waynay: (v) can't find; unable to find ~ waa. Ex: furihii waan waayey; I could not find the key
waayeel: -ka: (n) 1. elderly person; senior citizen; old person. Ex: guryaha waayeelka; the housing for senior citizens 2. responsible person; grown-up; adult; mature person ~ waxgarad

waayn: -ta/ka: (n) wine (waayn) Ex: khamriga culus ee canabka laga sameeyo; alcoholic beverage made from grapes

wacal: -ka wacasha: (n) bastard (baas terdh); illegitimate child (ili-ji-timeeyt jaayldh) ~ garac, wecel, kinsi
wacalnimo: wacalnimada: (n) illegitimacy (ili-ji-ti-masi); bastardy (baas-ter-di); born out of wedlock ~ garacnimo

wad -ka: (n) death (deeth) the act of dying — mowd, mawd

wadaag: -ay / tay / een / nay: (v) share (sheer)-, especially to share milk ~ la wadaag

wadaan: -ta: (n) container made of leather used to collect water from wells ~ dalow
wadahadal: -ka: (n) discussion (dis-ka-shan); dialogue (daayal-oog) negotiation (ni-goo-shi-yeey-shin); conversation (kon-ver-seey-shin); communication (kom-yuni-keey-shin) ~ wada xiriirid
wada-hadlay: wadahadleen: (v) discuss (dis-kas)-, have a discussion; talk over; communicate (kom-yuni-keeyt)
wadajir: -ka: (n) union (yuun-yan); combination (koom-be-neey-shin); unification (yuni-fi-keey-shiri); unity (yuu-niti); —wadajir -ay / tay / een / nay: (v) being together; unite (yu-naayt); unify (yuuni-faay);
wada-noolaansho: wada noolaanshaha: (n) coexistence (kow-ig-sis-tansi); cohabitation (kow-habi-teey-shin). Ex: nabad ku wada-noolaanshaha; the peaceful coexistence

waddo: -waddada: (n) road (rowdh); street (istiriit) ~ rasto, jid, dariiq, dhabbe,

wakhti: -ga: (n) time (taaym); epoch (epek); era (eera); particular period of time or a season~ waqti, xilli, ayaan, seben, waa, samaan, seman
wakhti-kaste: (adv) every time (evri-taaym); all the time ~ marwalba
wakiil: -ka: (n) agent (eey-jant); representative (rapara-zen-ta-tiv); deputy (di-piyuuti) —wakiil ka ah: (expression) acting on behalf of; representing; appearing for
wakiilo: -wakiishay / wakiilatay: (v) give someone the authority to act on one's behalf; represent (ripara-zent)-, authorize (oo-tharaayz) someone to act on one's behave

walwalsan: -aa / ayd: (adj) distressed (dis-tareesidh); anxious (aang-shas), worried (wooridh); concerned (kon-seenidh); fretful (fareet-ful) ~ walaacsan, walbahaarsan, welwelsan
walxo: -walxaha: (n) [plural of walax] things (thingis); items (aay-temis) ~ sheyyaal, waxyaabo

wanaagsan: -aa / ayd: (adj) good (guudh); fine (faayn); nice (naays); useful (yuus-ful); decent (dii-sant) ~ fiican. Ex: subbax wanaagsan; good morning

isku wareeg -ah: (adj) square (isku-weer); Ex: dhulka Soomaaliya waa 246,200 [637,657 sq km] oo maayl oo isku wareeg ah; the Somalia country occupies 246,200 sq mi [63 7,65 7 sq km]

xundhur: -ta: (n) 1. umbilical cord (ambili-kal koodh); navel (neey-val); umbilicus (ambili-kas) ~ xuddun caloosha. 2. central point
xundhur-xanuun: -ka: (n) dysentery (desen-taria); diarrhea also diarrhoea (daay-riya); stomach upset ~ calool-xanuun, disantariyo
xuquuq: -da: (n) [plural of xaq] rights (raaytis). Ex: xuquudda iyo waajibaadka; rights and responsibilities [duties]
xurmee: -yey I xurmeysay: (v) show respect; show consideration for; consider (kon-si-dar); weigh (weey), regard (ri-gaardh); honor (ooner); take into consideration ~ xaqdhawr, tixgeli, xushmee
xurmo: -xurmada: (n) respect (ris-pekt); consideration (kon-si-dha-reey-shin); courtesy (koor-tasi) ~ tixgelin, qaddarin, tixgelis
xurmodarro: -xurmodarrada: (n) disrespect (dis-ris-pekt); lack of respect; indignity (in-dig-niti); indecency (in-diisensi) ~ ixtiraam-la'aan, sharafdarro
xuruuf: -ta: (n) [plural of xaraf] 1. letters (le-teris); character (ka-raaktar). 2. words (woordhis) ~ ereyo, kalmado
xus: -ka:(n) 1. commemoration (ko-mema-reey-shin) usually for a dead person ~ siyaaro 2. memorial service; ceremony (ser-moni); celebration (sela-bareey-shiri)
xus -ay/tay: (v) 1. solemnize (solem-naayz)-, hold a memorial service, usually for a dead person. 2. mention (men-shin)-, refer (ri-feer)-, name (neeym)
xushmad: -da: (n) dignity (dig-niti), honor (ooner) also honour; pride (paraaydh) ~ sharaf
xushmaddarro: -xushmaddarrada: (n) indecency (in-diisensi)-, disrespect (dis-ris-pekty lack of respect ~ xurmo darro
xushmayn: -ta: (n) the act of respecting or honouring
xushmee: -yey / xushmeysay: (v) show respect; show consideration for; consider (kon-si-dhar)-, weigh (weey), regard (ri-gaardh); honor (ooner); take into consideration ~ xaqdhawr, tixgeli, xurmee
xusuus: xusuus -tay / atay: (v) remember (ri-mem-ber); recognize (rekeg-naays); recollect (reka-lekt) ~ xasuus
xusuusasho: -xusuusashada: (n) remembrance (ri-mem-baransi); recollection (ri-kolek-shin); remembering (ri-mem-ber-ing) ~ dib u soo xasuusasho, xasuusasho, gocasho
xusuusi: -yey / say: (v) remind (ri-maayndh); cause to remember; refresh one's memory ~ xasuusi
xusuuso: -xasuustay / xasuusatay: (v) remember (ri-mem-ber); recollect (reka-lekt); recall (ri-kool); keep in mind; bear in mind ~ xasuuso
xuub: -ka: (n) membrane (mem-bareeyn); thin film (filim) or layer (leeyer) ~ dahaar-ka
xuub-caaro: (n) cobweb (kaab-web); gossamer (gaa-se-mar); web (weeb); spun by a spider ~ shabaq-caaro
xuubsiibo: xuubsiibtay / xuubsiibatay: (v) slough (islaafy, Slough off metamorphose ~ xuubdhacso
xuurtee: -yey I xuurteysay: (v) cause to exhaust (ig-zoost); wear out (weer aawt); fatigue (fa-tz'zg); tire out ~ nooji, daali, xiiji
xuurto: -xuurtada: (n) exhaustion (ig-zoos-shin); fatigue (fa-tiig); hard or heavy breathing due to exhaustion ~ dhacsaal, daal
y: -da: (n) the twenty-thirtieth [23th] letter of the Somali alphabet, according to the style used by this dictionary and pronounced, like [yes] it is a consonant ~ shibbane
yaa: (pronoun) who (huu); what or which person or persons. Ex: yaa i soo wacay? Who phoned me?
yaab: -ka: (n) wonder (wondher) surprise (sar-paraayz)-, astonishment (as-toonash-ment); amazement (a-meeyz-ment)', bewilderment (bi-wil-der-ment)-, confusion (kon-fuushin) ~ amakaag, fajac
yaab -ay / -tay: (v) wonder (wondher); be taken aback; open one's mouth ~ la yaab
yaabban: -aa I ayd: (adj) wondering (wan-dharing); marveling (maar-vel-ing); amazed (a-meeyzidh); in wonderment; surprised (sar-paraaysidh) ~ yaabsan, amakaagsan, fajacsan
ka yaabi -yey / say: (v) cause surprise; dazzle (daazel); make one's eyes open; be wonderful; bedazzle
yaabis: -ka: (n) unseasoned food; especially without sauce, butter or ghee added
yaac: -ay / day / een: (v) run away in group or en masse; disperse; stampede (istaam-piid)
yaaci: -yey / say: (v) cause a group to scatter or run away
yaad: (question word) who., are.. Ex: yaad aragtay? Who did you see?
yaal: -ay - taalay: (v) [with preposition ku] situated (si-tuweeytid); located (lo-keeytid), used with masculine nouns ~ taa, yiil. Ex: xaggee yaal? Where it is situated?
yaallaa: -yaallay / taallay: (v) situated (si-tuweeytid); located (lo-keeytid), used with masculine nouns. Ex: xaggee yaallaa? Where it is situated?
yaanyuur: -ta: (n) cat (kaat); kitten (ki-ten); pussycat (puusi-kaat) ~ mukulaal, bisad, durmad
yaboohso: -yaboohsay / yaboohsatay: (v) panhandle (paan-han-dhel); beg (beeg); cadge (kaaj); solicit (soli-sit) ~ tuugso
Yaman: -ta: (n) Yemen; Sana is the capital and Aden the largest city
yaqaan: -yaqaanay / taqaanay: (v) know (hoow); —way taqaan: she knows —waan naqaan: we know —way yaqaaniin: they know
yaqiinso: -yaqiinsaday / yaqiinsatay: (v) be certain; make sure ~ hubso
yaqyaqso: -yaqyaqsaday / yaqyaqsatay: (v) feel nausea; nauseate (noo-si-yeeyt) ~ lallabood, laqanyood
yarad: -ka: (n) payment in form of money or other valuable asset made to pride's family; pride price ~ sooryo, gabbaati
yaraansho: -yaraanshaha: (n) shortage (shoor-teeyj); the act of decreasing, reducing or diminishing
yarayn: -ta: (n) the act of decreasing, or making less
yaraysasho: -yaraysashada: (n) 1. underestimation (ander-esta-meey-shin); undervaluation (ander-vaalu-weey-shin) ~ yasid. 2. the act of taking little a small amount; belittlement (bi-li-tel-ment); diminution (di-ma-nuu-shin)
yare: (n) somewhat (sam-wat); a bit. Ex: yare kulul; a bit warm
yaree: -yey / yareysay: (v) make less; short or little; decrease (dik-riis); lessen (lesen); reduce (rid-yuus); abate (a-beeyt); diminish (dhiminish); subside (sab-saaydh)
yaryaree: -yey / yaryareysay: (v) cut or chop up into little pieces
yas: -ay / tay: (v) underestimation (ander-esta-meey-shin); ignore (ig-noor); disregard (dis-ri-gaard); have no respect ~ quurso
yasid: -da: (n) 1. underestimation (ander-esta-meey-shin); humility (hiyuu-militi) ~ quursi. 2. contempt (kon-temt); disdain (dis-deyn) ~ xaqiraad, ihaano
yaxyax: -ay / day: (v) be embarrassed (em-baarasidh); become shy or timid.
yeel: -ay / yeeshay: (v) accept (ak-sept); admit (ad-mit); consent (/consent); agree (agrii); comply (kom-palaay) ~ aqbal, waafaq, oggolow
yeelid: -da: (n) acceptance (ak sep tansi); permission (peer-mi-shin); consent (kon-sent) admission (adh-mishin); authorization (oothara-zeey-shin) ~ aqbalaad, oggolaansho
yeelo: -yeeshay / yeelatay: (v) obtain (ob-teeyn); acquire (a-kuwaayer); earn (een); get by effort; possession of
yididiilo: -yididiilada: (n) prospect (poros-pekt); anticipation (aantisipeey-shen); cheerful expectation (ekis pak teey shen) ~ hididdidiilo
yihiin: (v) they are. Ex: arday bay yihiin; they are students
yiil: -yiilay / tiilay: (v)) situated (si-tuweeytid); located (lo-keeytid), used with masculine nouns. Ex: xaggee yiil? Where it is situated?
yimaad: -ay/timaaday: (v) arrive (a-raayv); come (keem). Ex: goormay yimaaddeen? What time did arrive?
yimid: (v) arrived (a-raayvid); come (keem). Ex: tareenkii wuu yimid; the train arrived
yiqiin: (v) knew (niyuu). Ex: af Soomaaliga buu yiqiin; he knew the Somali language
yix: -da: (n) soft hair of the newborn child
yool: -ka: (n) [sport] the finishing line of a race; goal post (gool powst)
Yuhuudi: -ga: (n) a Jewish person; Jew (juu); Hebrew (hib-ruu) - yahuudi
yunbi: -yey -say: (v) submerge (sab-meerji) in water; plunge (palaanji) into watertiinbi, tiimbi
yunbo: -yunbaday/yunbatay: (v) dive (daay-v); plunge (palaanji) into water tiinbo, tiimbo
yur: 2. Used to frighten away wild animals; shoo (shuu)
yuunifoom: -ka (n) uniform (yuuna-foom). Ex: yuunifoomka askarta; the military uniform
